_pdbx_entry_details.sequence_details           
;RESIDUE NUMBERS 94-98 IN CHAINS A, B AND RESIDUE NUMBERS 64, 99-104 IN CHAINS C, D ARE SIMPLY SKIPPED.
CHAINS A AND D, CHAINS B AND C WERE EXPRESSED AS A SINGLE-CHAIN CONSTRUCT, AND WERE DIVIDED IN THE CRYSTAL STRUCTURE TO MATCH PREVIOUS CRYSTAL STRUCTURES AND BECAUSE THE LINKER WAS NOT VISIBLE. ONE FUSION PROTEIN COMPRISES CHAIN A, THE LINKER, CHAIN D AND C-TERMINAL TAIL, ANOTHER FUSION PROTEIN COMPRISES CHAIN B, THE LINKER, CHAIN C AND C-TERMINAL TAIL. THE LINKER IS NGGGGSGGGGSGGGGSGGGGS AND C-TERMINAL TAIL SSALEHHHHHH.
FOR CHAIN E, F, THE SEQUENCE DATABASE REFERENCE DOES NOT CURRENTLY EXIST.
;
